cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use HWE Bench in research, please cite it as below."
title: "HWE Bench: An Unbounded Benchmark for LLM Hardware Development on RISC-V"
authors:
  - family-names: Bonetto
    given-names: Felipe Sens
    email: felipesensbonetto@gmail.com
type: software
repository-code: "https://github.com/FeSens/auto-arch-tournament"
url: "https://hwebench.com"
version: v1
date-released: "2026-05-15"
keywords:
  - benchmark
  - large language models
  - RISC-V
  - CPU design
  - microarchitecture
  - formal verification
  - FPGA
  - hardware engineering
abstract: >-
  HWE Bench measures LLM hardware-development capability by having
  models propose and implement RISC-V CPU microarchitectures, scored
  by CoreMark fitness (Fmax × IPC) on a real FPGA under riscv-formal
  correctness gates. Unlike saturable benchmarks such as SWE-bench,
  HWE Bench has no ceiling — fitness can keep climbing as long as
  models keep finding better microarchitecture. An arXiv preprint
  describing the methodology in detail is in preparation; in the
  interim, please cite the repository.
